      "comment": "DANGEROUS (9) made a winning return after more than three months when he drew wide and raced parked but was too strong last start, getting home by 1.6 metres at Bendigo. May need an ounce of luck from this tricky draw but has won both previous visits to this venue. METEOR MOTH (7) is flying at present with two successive wins to his name, most recently at Melton a week-and-a-half ago. Building a strong record at this distance so is a big chance to keep the ball rolling.  MY ULTIMATE JIMMY NZ (4) scored an authoritative win last start over this distance, getting home by 7 metres to take his record here to eight from 12. Tackles some strong opposition here but can perform well again. FORTY LOVE (6) is worth some thought after his last-start fourth after racing parked at Melton.",
